Package productlinetracker

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Item
    The Item interface implements the methods of the item's name, manufacturer, and ID to the classes that utilizes them.
    MultimediaControl
    The MultimediaControl interface is where the functions of an audio player and a movie player are obtained.
    ScreenSpec
    The ScreenSpec interface is where a Product's screen resolution, refresh rate, and response time are obtained.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioPlayer
    The AudioPlayer class is where the program captures the details of an audio player.
    Controller
    The Controller Class handles the events and the functionality of the program.
    Employee
    The Employee class allows users to input their full name and create a user id of their first name, a period, and then their surname, which will be an email address of their first initial and last name.
    Main
    The program is a software made in JavaFX where it tracks the number and types of products being made.
    MoviePlayer
    The MoviePlayer class is where the information of a Product that is a MoviePlayer is obtained.
    Product
    The Product class implements the basic functionality that all items on a production line should have.
    ProductionRecord
    The ProductionRecord class is used to store information about the product being made, including generating a unique serial number for each product produced.
    Screen
    The Screen class is where the Product's screen information is made.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ItemType
    The ItemType enum is where the the enums for each item types are created.
    MonitorType
    The program is a software made in JavaFX where it tracks the number and types of products being made.
